cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and specifically on salient object detection, which falls under the category of image processing and analysis. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.LG (machine learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new deep network architecture, which could also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) and cs.MM (multimedia).
